['Requirements:', 'content', 'BA/BS degree required. Masters, MBA, or Ph.D. is a plus;
5+ years of experience in Enterprise account management, Enterprise sales, and customer success for a SaaS company with a recurring revenue model and/or management consulting within a life sciences practice. Experience working for a technology startup is a plus;
A basic understanding of biopharma operations, drug discovery and development, and the R&D outsourcing market;
Experience negotiating 6-7 figure recurring revenue contracts, driving renewals, cross-sells and upsells as an individual contributor
Previous experience carrying and achieving revenue quotas within key Enterprise and fortune 500 accounts, with ability to manage internal resources on a dotted line basis
Strong verbal and written communications skills; able to effectively communicate to executives in a Board room setting;
Excellent analytical skills; ability to build and deliver compelling data-driven business cases, demos, and presentations to a technical, as well as operational audience at all levels of the organization;
Strong desire to work in a high-growth, fast-paced organization with a performance-driven culture;
Adaptability and flexibility to changing priorities;
Attention to detail, highly organized, and with ability to work simultaneously on multiple accounts priorities;
Previous experience with Salesforce CRM and/or other salesforce suite of products
Willingness to travel to customer sites depending on accounts being managed']

['About the Role', 'The position will report to our General Counsel and will manage our Legal Operations & Privacy Program Manager. Houzz is looking for a business-minded and team-oriented privacy attorney to join our Legal team and lead our privacy and information security function. This person will be a key advisor to our business teams across the company. The role will also partner with our Security team to continue to improve our information security posture. This role will help define and drive the processes that ensure that data is managed securely and in compliance with all relevant laws. Depending on the level of seniority and experience, the person may also be appointed to be the company’s Privacy Officer or Chief Privacy Officer.', '', 'What You’ll Do', 'Advise the business teams, including the product and engineering teams, on all relevant data privacy and security laws and regulations;
Advise the product, sales, and marketing teams on TCPA, CAN-SPAM and other communications laws worldwide;
Monitor developments in privacy, security, and other consumer protection laws in all of the jurisdictions where Houzz operates (including GDPR and other global privacy and data protection laws);
Partner with product counsels responsible for supporting specific business teams by providing “horizontal” privacy support;
Negotiate privacy-related provisions within commercial transactions;
Own relevant internal and external policies and guidelines;
Manage the Legal Operations & Privacy Program Manager;
Assist with the development and enforcement of compliance programs related to privacy, payments (PCI), marketing, communications and consumer protection regulations; and
Help respond to, investigate, and manage any potential data and security incidents.', '', 'At a Minimum, We’d Like You to Have', 'At least 6 years of relevant experience, including startup or other in-house experience, preferably at a consumer internet platform or SaaS business;
Subject matter expertise in state, federal and international privacy and security laws;
Strong written and verbal communication skills;
A technical background or be tech-savvy and curious about learning new platforms;
Experience with working with and supervising outside counsel and managing legal budgets;
Ability to multitask, prioritize, and work efficiently while collaborating on multiple deals, and escalate issues when needed;
Enthusiasm for the Houzz platform; and
A JD and admission to a state bar.', '', "Ideally, You'll Also Have"]

['ABOUT PLACER.AI:', 'Placer.ai is a fast-growing big data startup led by seasoned executives and repeat entrepreneurs who are building the world's first "Google Analytics for the physical world." Placer.ai’s platform provides instant visibility into any property in the U.S., presenting accurate details about visitation patterns and demographic breakdowns of visitors. Placer.ai’s customers can see where visitors have been before, where they go afterwards, where they typically go for sports, entertainment, groceries, etc., and what their interests are. Placer.ai's A.I.-based SaaS platform replaces archaic solutions such as manual surveys, installed cameras and other people-counting systems, creating a blue ocean market of more than $100B.', 'Placer.ai has grown 3x year-over-year for the past 3 years, counting more than 1,900 paying customers across a range of industries, including 2 of the world’s top-10 retailers, 2 of the top-10 CPG firms worldwide, a world’s top hospitality firm, 2 of the world’s top-10 commercial real estate (CRE) firms and 2 of the world’s top multinational asset managers and hedge funds. Placer.ai has just raised $100M for Unicorn ($1B+) valuation in Series C funding.', 'SUMMARY:', 'The GTM Strategy & Operations team works directly with Placer’s most senior GTM leaders to support Placer’s growth, cracking today’s problems while also balancing our need to build for the long-term. We develop and operationalize a clear strategy and framework for market prioritization, pricing, organizational design, and generate insights to drive growth and funnel efficiencies. The GTM Strategy & Ops team also offers a unique ability to work across teams to see how a hyper-scaling startup operate.', 'As a Strategy & Ops Associate, you will be highly analytical, technical, and operational, with a clear bias towards driving results. You’ll report to the Director of GTM Strategy & Operations and get the opportunity to be mentored by two other experienced team members.', 'WHAT YOU’LL DO:', 'Quantitative analysis & modeling: perform extensive analysis on key metrics for the GTM Teams (sales development, sales, customer success, and marketing) and deliver actionable insights that help drive growth and funnel efficiencies;
Research: perform research to help refine our understanding and measurement of our Total Addressable Market (TAM) , assess emerging verticals’ use cases to support new market initiatives;
Functional partnership: provide data supporting GTM leaders to determine the company’s hiring plans & optimal organizational design;
Planning / reporting: help develop and track critical GTM metrics associated with each major project and develop robust processes to maintain models and reporting.', 'REQUIREMENTS:', 'Bachelor’s degree, in business, economics, accounting or a quantitative degree
2 years min. experience preferred in investment banking, management consulting, revenue & growth strategy functions at a technology company, or equivalent experience as a business analyst
Strong analytical skills: you have a data-driven mentality and high attention to detail; you are excited to dig through data to get actionable insights
Excellent modeling skills: you have strong modeling intuition and a good understanding of how to decompose a complex problem into a model’s building blocks. Top notch modeling skills are a must: you’ll be working in Google Sheets / Excel on a daily basis and be performing analyses that require complex data manipulation
Get things done mentality: you have a track record of leading projects to completion and following up to ensure success
Flexibility: you are comfortable working in a fast-paced remote startup environment that will require you to manage competing priorities, pivot quickly and often, and communicate often on progress to your team members. You’re excited to take on big ambiguous problems that haven’t been tackled before']
